  "response": "To dress like it's 1990 for men, consider these style elements:\n\n1. Clothing items:\n- High-waisted jeans (often acid-washed or stone-washed)\n- Oversized denim jackets\n- Baggy or tapered pants\n- Windbreakers or colorful athletic jackets\n- Polo shirts with popped collars\n- Graphic t-shirts\n- Sweaters tied around waist\n- Flannel shirts\n\n2. Shoes:\n- White sneakers (like Nike Air or Reebok)\n- High-top sneakers\n- Converse\n- Doc Martens\n\n3. Accessories:\n- Baseball caps (often worn backwards)\n- Sunglasses with large frames\n- Thin leather belts\n- Watch with a large face\n\n4. Colors and patterns:\n- Bright, bold colors\n- Neon shades\n- Color blocking\n- Geometric patterns\n- Pastel tones\n\n5. Hairstyles:\n- Mullet\n- Longer hair\n- Slicked-back hair\n- Side-parted styles\n\nLook at references from TV shows like \"Fresh Prince of Bel-Air\" or music videos from that era for authentic inspiration.",
